This article is a transcript of a press gaggle with White House Deputy Press Secretary Bill Burton aboard Air Force One. Burton provides information about President Obama's upcoming visit to Costa Mesa, California, where he will hold a town hall meeting at the Orange County Fairgrounds. The President's remarks will focus on restoring the nation's prosperity and making strategic decisions for long-term growth. Burton also mentions the high unemployment rate and foreclosure numbers in California. He states that the President will not be announcing any new programs or initiatives during this visit, but will discuss the recovery plan and budget. Additionally, Burton mentions that the President is working on setting up a resolution authority and regulatory reform. He also addresses questions about the timeline for the Afghanistan and Pakistan policy review, California's allocation from the recovery plan, and the recent controversy over AIG bonuses. Burton concludes by mentioning some of the local officials who will be joining the President at the town hall meeting.